body:
Hot Take 🔥

MCU is likely going to RUIN Monica Rambeau, the OG Captain Marvel to prop up this Captain Marvel instead of oh idk saving her for something else or hell put in Luke Cage for a bit since we know they don’t acknowledge the TV side & she was on a Team with him in the comics. Plus I’m not gonna wanna see Monica who is a far more intriguing yet underutilized character play second fiddle to Carol with Brie “U Better not look at me with that DISGUSTING Male Gaze” Larson who has if I recall already driven the white demographic away with her unprofessional comments. But what I know I also think BvS is a Fantastically Underrated & Shunned Film for Actually Trying something different than the rather streamlined by the numbers No Villains Living Allowed for long MCU which I liked decently in the beginning.

summary: No offense to Jude Law but I hope to god that Carol Danvers (Brie Larson/Captain Marvel) isn't fucking paired romantically with...
body:
No offense to Jude Law but I hope to god that Carol Danvers (Brie Larson/Captain Marvel) isn’t fucking paired romantically with Mar-vell (Jude Law) because

a) when Carol Danvers was originally introduced in the comics she was a fucking flat ass character purely because she was romantic fodder for Mar-vell

b) we do NOT need another male mentor/female mentee romantic relationship thank you
